						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab (A. 36) in the Bijapur Museum.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa (undated).</p>						

						<p>This inscription in <hi rend="bold">Nāgarī</hi> characters is partly in Sanskrit and partly in Kannaḍa. It refers to <hi rend="bold">Siṁgaṇa-bhūpati</hi> and registers a grant of land. The village <hi rend="bold">Pauṭhage</hi> situated in the division of <hi rend="bold">Tardavāḍi One-thousand</hi> is mentioned. <hi rend="bold">Jētādēvī</hi> is mentioned. </p>						

